# .offensive-content-blocklist — patterns to flag as offensive content
#
# Each non-blank, non-comment line is a POSIX extended regex.
# Matched content triggers a scan-offensive violation.
#
# Format:
#   - Lines starting with '#' are comments.
#   - Plain regex lines are hard-block patterns (exit 1).
#   - Prefix a regex with 'warn:' for a soft-block (exit 2, asks the user).
#
# This file is write-protected by the block-dotenv.js PreToolUse hook —
# Claude Code cannot edit this file. Add patterns manually when genuinely needed.
#
# See docs/scan-outbound.md "Offensive Content Filter" section for details.

# Hard-block — always rejects
# example_pattern_here

# Soft-block — high false-positive risk, asks the user
# warn:example_warn_pattern_here
